asx4000RedFabricEntry.name: asx4000RedFabricEntry
asx4000RedFabricEntry.description: A table entry containing fabric information.

asx4000RedFabricAdminMode.name: asx4000RedFabricAdminMode
asx4000RedFabricAdminMode.description: The admin mode for this fabric

asx4000RedFabricOperState.name: asx4000RedFabricOperState
asx4000RedFabricOperState.description: The oper state for this fabric

asx4000RedFabricPendingAdminMode.name: asx4000RedFabricPendingAdminMode
asx4000RedFabricPendingAdminMode.description: This variable is used to set the value for admin mode for this fabric.The asx4000RedFabricAdminMode variable is set to this value on setting the asx4000RedFabricCommit variable

asx4000RedFabricCommittedState.name: asx4000RedFabricCommittedState
asx4000RedFabricCommittedState.description: This variable indicates if a command has been committed for this particular fabric.

asx4000RedFabricCloningState.name: asx4000RedFabricCloningState
asx4000RedFabricCloningState.description: The cloning state of this fabric

asx4000RedFabricSwitchCommand.name: asx4000RedFabricSwitchCommand
asx4000RedFabricSwitchCommand.description: User initiated command at fabric level switchovers. Setting this variable with the following values causes the switchover to happen as explained. active - causes a switchover to active for this fabric standy - causes a switchover to standby for this fabric Note this object is write-only and reading it will result in implementation-specific results.

asx4000RedFabricRedundancyState.name: asx4000RedFabricRedundancyState
asx4000RedFabricRedundancyState.description: This is the current redundancy state of th efabric. The possible values for this variable are dependent upon whether the fabric is protected or not, and whether it supports passive or active redundancy.

asx4000RedFabricGroupCommit.name: asx4000RedFabricGroupCommit
asx4000RedFabricGroupCommit.description: A command to commit a fabric group configuration Note this object is write-only and reading it will result in implementation-specific results.

asx4000RedPortCardEntry.name: asx4000RedPortCardEntry
asx4000RedPortCardEntry.description: A table entry containing portcard information.

asx4000RedPortCardFabIndex.name: asx4000RedPortCardFabIndex
asx4000RedPortCardFabIndex.description: The fabric index this portcard is connected to

asx4000RedPortCardIndex.name: asx4000RedPortCardIndex
asx4000RedPortCardIndex.description: The netmod pair index of this portcard

asx4000RedPortCardCloningState.name: asx4000RedPortCardCloningState
asx4000RedPortCardCloningState.description: The netmod pair index of this portcard

asx4000RedundancyGroupTable.name: asx4000RedundancyGroupTable
asx4000RedundancyGroupTable.description: This is the Redundancy Group table.

asx4000RedundancyGroupEntry.name: asx4000RedundancyGroupEntry
asx4000RedundancyGroupEntry.description: This is a Redundancy Group entry, which represents the configuration of a working and protection fabric and their associated portcards.

asx4000RedGroupName.name: asx4000RedGroupName
asx4000RedGroupName.description: This is the redundancy group name. A redundancy group name identifies a working and protection fabric and their associated portcards are a single unit.

asx4000RedGroupRevertMode.name: asx4000RedGroupRevertMode
asx4000RedGroupRevertMode.description: This is the revert mode for this redundancy group. If the revert mode is on(1), automatic switchover from the protection fabric to the working fabric will occur if the working fabric becomes available. Setting the revert mode to off(2) disables this behavior.

asx4000RedGroupQualifyTimer.name: asx4000RedGroupQualifyTimer
asx4000RedGroupQualifyTimer.description: This is the qualification timer in minutes for this redundancy group. For fabric and portcards that support active redundancy, asx4000RedGroupQualifyTimer is the number of minutes that an errored fabric or portcard must undergo error-free loopback testing before being declared as an available fabric or portcard. This timer has no effect for fabrics and portcards that do not support active redundancy.

asx4000RedGroupErrorThreshold.name: asx4000RedGroupErrorThreshold
asx4000RedGroupErrorThreshold.description: This is the loopback error threshold in cells for this redundancy group. For fabrics and portcards that support active redundancy, if the number of loopback cell errors equals or exceeds asx4000RedGroupErrorThreshold during the past asx4000RedGroupErrorBlockSize loopback cells, then an error condition is declared for the loopback components. Setting this error threshold to zero (0) disables error checking. The maximum value is the error block size asx4000RedGroupErrorBlockSize.

asx4000RedGroupErrorBlockSize.name: asx4000RedGroupErrorBlockSize
asx4000RedGroupErrorBlockSize.description: This is the loopback error block size in cells for this redundancy group. For fabrics and portcards that support active redundancy, this is the number of consecutive loopback cells over which the error threshold asx4000RedGroupErrorThreshold will be applied.

asx4000RedNetmodEntry.name: asx4000RedNetmodEntry
asx4000RedNetmodEntry.description: A table entry containing netmod information.

asx4000RedNetmodFabIndex.name: asx4000RedNetmodFabIndex
asx4000RedNetmodFabIndex.description: The fabric index this netmod is connected to

asx4000RedNetmodIndex.name: asx4000RedNetmodIndex
asx4000RedNetmodIndex.description: The netmod index of this netmod

asx4000RedNetmodRedundancyState.name: asx4000RedNetmodRedundancyState
asx4000RedNetmodRedundancyState.description: This is the current redundancy state of the netmod. The possible values for this variable are dependent upon whether the fabric to which this netmod is connection to is protected or not, and whether it supports passive or active redundancy.

redundancyFabricSwitchover.name: redundancyFabricSwitchover
redundancyFabricSwitchover.description: This trap reports the change of active fabric due to an automatic or revertive switchover. The fabric identified by the trap variable asx4000RedFabricIndex is the newly active fabric.

redundancyFabricErrorCleared.name: redundancyFabricErrorCleared
redundancyFabricErrorCleared.description: This trap reports the clearing of the active redundancy fabric error for the fabric identified by the trap variable asx4000RedFabricIndex.

redundancyFabricErrorDetected.name: redundancyFabricErrorDetected
redundancyFabricErrorDetected.description: This trap reports the declaration of the active redundancy fabric error for the fabric identified by the trap variable asx4000RedFabricIndex.

redundancyNetmodErrorCleared.name: redundancyNetmodErrorCleared
redundancyNetmodErrorCleared.description: This trap reports the clearing of the active redundancy netmod error for the netmod identified by the trap variables asx4000RedNetmodFabIndex and asx4000RedNetmodIndex.

redundancyNetmodErrorDetected.name: redundancyNetmodErrorDetected
redundancyNetmodErrorDetected.description: This trap reports the declaration of the active redundancy netmod error for the netmod identified by the trap variables asx4000RedNetmodFabIndex and asx4000RedNetmodIndex.
